      {
        "id": 4047679,
        "name": "Nick Christie",
        "username": "Nick_Christie",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/nick_christie/{size}/2729_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-04-07T10:25:09.537Z",
        "cooked": "<p>William will undoubtedly have plenty to say about this beautiful wine in the months and years to come. I do not wish to <em>pigeon</em> all his best takes, but I do want to relate his emphasis that this vintage represents his fifth year as a winemaker. And just how important that relationship of time &amp; focus &amp; learning is to being an artisan. That resonates, doesn\u2019t it? No matter how much intelligence and drive with which one begins one\u2019s craft, the lessons &amp; experiences of navigating so many variables from field to final product represent such an essential period of craftsmanship. They elevate the winemaker.</p>\n<p>We drank this from bottle, although given how freshly bottled it had been, you could say this basically transferred from <em>garage to maison</em> via bottle form. This <em>Les Foucheres</em> has such a fresh, romantic nose. Full of soft, ripe red fruits and an array of flowers. The wine is in balance. There is no hint of manipulation. There is undoubtedly so much technique, but the technique is hidden inside the winemaking. It bears that level of sophistication.</p>\n<p>William\u2019s love and passion for agriculture has inspired much of our dialogue these past few years; it\u2019s certainly the facet of his posts here that has excited me the most. What is so awesome about his winemaking career is seeing the practical, tangible products of that love. This wine has a purity and an elegance and it also smells like it came from <em>somewhere</em>, somewhere special.</p>\n<p>William is such a brilliant voice in Burgundy that even a medium success in Chambolle would be worth celebrating. To have this '21 vintage be a <em>serious</em> success is all the more exciting. I could not be happier for him.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/0/a/0ad7c46c32a5f1181ebbeda5aa04eecccdbef2b6.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/0ad7c46c32a5f1181ebbeda5aa04eecccdbef2b6\" title=\"20230331_202410\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/0/a/0ad7c46c32a5f1181ebbeda5aa04eecccdbef2b6_2_375x500.jpeg\" alt=\"20230331_202410\" data-base62-sha1=\"1xV3lqtssHptaDfLAZBGEEtuC9g\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/0/a/0ad7c46c32a5f1181ebbeda5aa04eecccdbef2b6_2_375x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/0/a/0ad7c46c32a5f1181ebbeda5aa04eecccdbef2b6_2_562x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/0/a/0ad7c46c32a5f1181ebbeda5aa04eecccdbef2b6_2_750x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"938068\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">20230331_202410</span><span class=\"informations\">1920\u00d72560 146 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>",
